Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
check_noise(25.10)                                          check_noise(25.10)

Name
       check_noise  -  Performs several consistency and completeness checks on
       noise models specified for a design

Syntax
       check_noise

       [-help]

       [-all]

       [-check_only {receiver_no_propagation_model |  receiver_no_dc_tolerence
       |

       driver_no_current_source_model | driver_no_model}]

       [-instance_list <string>]

       [-instance_only {true | false}]

       [-pin_list <string>]

       [-type {receiver_model | driver_model}]

       [-unique {true | false}]

       [-verbose]

       [-view <string>]

       [ [ > | >> ] <filename> ]

       Performs  several  consistency  and completeness checks on noise models
       specified for a design. These checks help to ensure that the right  set
       of models are available for the SI analysis engine to perform crosstalk
       noise analysis.

       Note:  You  need to set setDelayCalMode -siAware to true before running
       the check_noise command.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -all   Displays all the debug information.

       -check_only {receiver_no_propagation_model | receiver_no_dc_tolerence |

              driver_no_current_source_model |  driver_no_model}"  Checks  the
              warning name. The following warnings are checked:

              * receiver_no_propagation_model:  Shows how many design pins are
                missing the receiver model for propagation.

              * receiver_no_dc_tolerence: Shows how many pins have no DC VH/VL
                tolerance specified.

              * driver_no_current_source_model: Shows how many design pins are
                missing the current source model.

              * driver_no_model: Specifies how many design  pins  are  missing
                the driver model.

       -instance_list <string>
              Specifies the instance name.

       -instance_only {true | false}
              Prints each instance only once.

       -pin_list <string>
              Specifies the instance pin names.

       -type {receiver_model | driver_model}
              Checks  the  presence  of a valid model type - receiver_model or
              driver_model. If the specified model is missing, a warning  will
              be issued.

              The  valid  receiver  models  are the models having vivo tables,
              such as, CDB, CCSN, ECSMN. The valid driver models are CDB, CCS,
              ECSM, NLDM, and UDN.

       -unique {true | false}
              Reports unique cells or pins for each power domain.

       -verbose
              Generates verbose details.

       -view <string>
              Specifies the view name.

       <>filename>
              Redirects output to a file.

       >><filename>
              Appends to an output file.

Examples
              * The following command generates the output as shown below:

                check_noise -type receiver_model

       **WARN:  (IMPESI-3125):  AAE_WARN:  The  analysis  view  specified   to
       check_noise  is  not  found  or  specified.  Checking view default_emu-
       late_view_setup.

